ble crimes but to all of humanity he cited world war ii as an example saying the people of europe are certainly familiar with what happens when the international community finds excuses not to act at the same time as commander in chief always preserve the right and the responsibility to act on behalf of america national security obama said conservative critics have said obama painted himself into corner with his statement last year that syria use of chemical weapons was red line that would change his approach to its civil war obama it is the world red line red line for us is we start seeing whole bunch of chemical weapons moving around or being utilized obama said in august 2012 that would change my calculus now critics on the right say he must respond to an alleged chemical weapons attack outside damascus by the syrian regime that kerry said killed more than people or lose credibility the administration and top congressional leaders attempted to blunt that criticism on tuesday during debate on capitol hill even house majority leader eric cantor the chamber no republican said any president would have drawn that red line based on international norms obama made that same argument on wednesday saying did set red line the world set red line the world set red line when governments representing 98 percent of the world population said the use of chemical weapons are abhorrent and passed treaty forbidding their use even when countries are engaged in war he said at joint news conference with swedish prime minister fredrik reinfeldt on the first day of trip that includes the summit in russia congress set red line when it ratified that treaty obama continued congress set red line when it indicated that in piece of legislation entitled the accountability act that some of the horrendous things that are happening on the ground there need to be answered for sounding exasperated obama added that was something just kind of made up did pluck it out of thin air there reason for it obama prods international community to act asked about whether he was seeking to save face obama insisted that my credibility is not on the line the international community credibility is on the line he framed the question for the united nations and the global community at large as are we going to try to find reason not to act and if that the case then think the world community should admit it opposition by russia syrian ally has scuttled and british efforts to get the security council to authorize military response against syrian president bashar regime inspectors returned from syria last week from their mission to confirm if chemical weapons were used but kerry said wednesday it would take three weeks for samples collected to analyzed and results announced respect the process obama said while standing next to reinfeldt who opposes military intervention without approval we agree that the international community can not be silent obama added saying also that the investigators had done heroic work noting the team mandate was only to determine the use of chemical weapons and not identify who used them obama repeated past statements that intelligence has confirmed chemical weapons use beyond any reasonable doubt and has further confirmed that regime was the source do think that we have to act because if we do we are effectively saying that even though we may condemn it and issue resolutions and so forth and so on somebody who is not shamed by resolutions can continue to act with impunity obama said international norms then begin to erode he added and other despots and authoritarian regimes can start looking and say something we can get away with he described the intended response as limited in time and in scope targeted at the specific task of degrading capabilities and deterring the use of those weapons again more than killed in syrian conflict the united nations has said more than people including many civilians have been killed since the popular uprising spiraled into 