ed states is capable of responding house minority leader nancy pelosi added that washington must respond to actions outside the circle of civilized human behavior syria missile strike what would happen next but in written statement later boehner said it is up to obama to make his case to the american people and their elected representatives including securing support from individual members all votes authorizing the use of military force are conscience votes for members and passage will require direct continuous engagement from the white house the speaker said no vote is scheduled before congress returns from its summer recess on monday kerry defended the delay to seek congressional authorization saying the move gives the united states time to make its case while adding pressure on this is working kerry said there are defections taking place there great uncertainty in syria we are building support greater understanding and would far rather be playing our hand than his at this point in time most of the focus of administration lobbying has been on the house in the senate democratic source familiar with majority leader harry reid thinking told cnn that reid is confident any authorization measure will pass his chamber the source said it is likely 60 votes will be needed to overcome filibuster and reid thinks the votes are there chief calls for end to security council the united nations has said more than people including many civilians have been killed in syria since popular uprising spiraled into civil war in syrian opposition activists reported another 77 dead on tuesday mostly in damascus and its suburbs new figures point to the staggering impact the war has had on the nation the number of syrians who have fled their country has risen above million the refugee agency reported an increase of nearly million people over the past 12 months but at the united nations ban urged security council members to await test results on the samples collected by inspectors we should a