nistic rhetoric of regime change and their ability to alter the dynamics of the militarized power game in syria ankara considers the alleged devastating use of chemical weapons by the regime as game changer and hopes that this tragedy will finally force the international community out of its comfort zone ankara wants the united states to launch military campaign that will be instrumental in toppling it sees any effective campaign as needing to either decapitate the syrian regime or at the very least weaken it substantially so that the opposition can make real inroads toward capturing damascus the turkish government fears that any alternative outcome will lead to emerging buoyed and gloating after having survived strike more from gps turkey jihadi dilemma meanwhile there are fears that even limited air strike if it happens will only add to intervention fatigue in the west this could end up reducing the likelihood of more expansive future military campaign in syria if this is the case then may become even more brutish in addition to further raising the humanitarian costs of the conflict may also become emboldened enough to act more aggressively against neighboring countries turkey would be particularly at risk having championed outside intervention in recent interview syrian deputy foreign minister faisal claimed that damascus would strike back not only at israel but also at syria neighbors jordan and turkey if they take part in any operation syria is believed to have 600 to 700 ballistic missiles the more advanced versions have range of about 700 kilometers meaning they can threaten most of turkey territory and reach its capital ankara they are potentially capable of carrying chemical and biological warheads turkey has no national means to protect itself against such an attack with nato assistance it has acquired six patriot batteries which are now set up near the syrian border but these interceptors have limited range of just 40 kilometers separately turkey is protected by nato missile defense umbrella but the effectiveness of this system especially against ballistic missiles equipped with chemical warheads remains unknown turkey border regions are additionally exposed to attacks by artillery and rocket strikes turkey best defense is the deterrence provided by its nato membership and ankara hopes that syria will resist from attacking turkey because such an aggression would trigger nato collective defense commitments ankara is now eagerly to see how things unfold on capitol hill and ultimately president obama decision on how to act having initially backed the and possibly option of comprehensive strike but for turkey own security interests token strike may not be worth strike at all
