w solely up to the military to bail the out and prevent the worst from happening more from cnn public against strike resolution to reduce the chances of things spinning out of control following military action obama has telegraphed his intentions to and to the syrian president allies the administration even specified to syria the primary weapon of choice cruise missiles rarely in the history of warfare do you see such an unambiguous transfer of critical information specifying end and means from the attacker to the defender even traditional arms controllers would be puzzled by the level of transparency that obama has exhibited but judged against the president stated objective which is to deliver shot across the bow this approach while bizarre and counterintuitive has been rational although or his allies could still miscalculate so what could military strike accomplish and what are the risks of going after the wrong targets or shooting too hard regime buildings obama could punish by destroying his defense or interior ministry air force intelligence directorate or other key government military and intelligence facilities but by now it is assumed that many of these buildings have been emptied and at least senior staffers have relocated true the strikes could still degrade the regime ability to hold large meetings and coordinate policy and strategy but destroying the regime central facilities carries some risks for example such facilities are considered powerful symbols of the regime and their destruction could leave humiliated and tempted to retaliate regime leadership if strikes end up killing leading regime figures the repressive capacity of the syrian government could be severely damaged however the death of relatives close associates could reduce incentive to head to the negotiating table after all the regime is very much family affair and might react brutally if his brother maher who heads both the republican guard and the army elite fourth armored division is killed while all regime figures have blood on their hands and should be held accountable for their crimes some might be more inclined than others to reach political deal when things start falling apart systematic elimination of all syrian regime figures by the united states would hurt policy command and control centers like to say that without communications all control is my desk and that is not very lethal weapon general power reportedly said way back in may in war the first thing an attacker wants to strike is his opponent command control communications and intelligence c3i capabilities with view to isolating the other side forces more from gps obama team has mishandled syria but if the military wipes out the c3i network of the syrian military most likely it could not with just cruise missiles there is real chance of the situation escalating under attack and unable to communicate and coordinate with the central leadership syrian commanders on the ground could resort to extreme measures if cornered such as launching chemical weapons therefore if and when the united states strikes whatever chance of averting escalation to chemical weapon use could depend on the continuous flow of syrian communications finally widespread destruction of syrian c3i could reduce the likelihood of early conflict termination if strikes back and war erupts because it would impede transmission of any order chemical weapons sites given the tremendous risks it bears repeating that the last target the united states wants to strike is chemical weapons sites hitting such targets could cause massive air contamination and lead to the deaths of many of the civilians that the united states is supposed to be trying to defend cruise missiles while highly accurate do not have the incendiary capability to destroy the poisonous substance this problem is exacerbated by the fact that chemical weapons are in some cases believed to be stored close to densely populated areas so what is left for the united states