ited states france and britain according to diplomats involved in the process russia and china which have united in the past to veto resolutions on syria have rejected any reference in the resolution to chapter of the charter provision that allows wide range of enforcement actions including the use of military force rather than syrian compliance failure russia has argued any discussion of punishment should take place only if and when such failure occurs according to diplomats who spoke on the condition of anonymity about the private discussions the framework agreement that secretary of state john kerry and russian foreign minister sergei lavrov reached last weekend is ambiguous on the question saying that in the event of compliance the security council should impose measures under chapter vii of the un charter kerry said tuesday that syrian disarmament would happen only with the united nations passing strong resolution it is important that the threat of force stay on the table in order to guarantee syrian compliance he said so we will continue to press this issue in the fox interview assad indicated that resolution was immaterial to syria decision whether they have chapter or don have this is politics between the great countries he said we obey the chemical weapons convention because we want to obey kerry and lavrov said in the agreement that they expect syria to turn over complete listing of its chemical weapons by saturday reference that the state department said wednesday referred to timeline rather than deadline the syrian list is to be turned over to the opcw which is then supposed to develop and approve process to take control of the syrian arsenal and ultimately destroy it assad said the timing is up to the opcw time is not our problem the problem is organization he said the only thing we have to do is to provide the information and make chemical sites accessible no problem we could do it tomorrow on related matters assad said the number of deaths in syria ongoing civil war more than by estimates has totaled about to he also said that up to 90 percent of rebel forces are backed by qaeda compared with estimates of about 10 percent asked whether he plans to be candidate in syrian elections scheduled for next year assad said he has made no decision
